Since you asked to see more on this makeover ☝️ here is behind the scenes of my recent class in Coeur D’Alene, Idaho ✈️

#GeodesicFoilayage 

💻 Class also available Online

Takeaways:

⭐️ Undercut a Blunt Bang with a Shag Shape over the top of it like layering Petals 🌹 

⭐️ Toast the Edges of the Face Frame with Round Ombré using over-direction forward 🍁 

⭐️ Use an Alkaline ColorMelt to shift the natural base at the same time as shadow rooting to soften the contrast between the natural dark base and the highlights 

Formulas:

Lightener @oligopro Cool Blonde 👱‍♀️ & @olaplex 

ColorMelt @schwarzkopfusa TBH
Root 5-16 & 6-06 1:1:1 6vol 
Mids-Ends 10-19 1:1:1 20vol
& Tone Softener 🎨 

Treatment @k18hair 💦

Would you believe me if I told you this was only 42 Foils that can be applied in 1 Hour ?!? 

Foilayage can be a frustratingly long technique and can easily take well over 100 foils and up to 3 hours to apply. I know, I’ve been there 😪

Over-foiling and ending up with a Rootie Platinum is hard not to do. 

Foilayage is supposed to be Balayage inside of Foils for the same visual placement with a lighter lift. If you think about it, we paint open-air on large triangles and can therefore apply a Balayage in about an hour.

I had the idea 💡 of breaking the Round Headshape into inter-locking Triangles, like a Geodesic Dome, and applying 2 Foils per Triangle 📐 One foil to replicate the surface painting and One Foil to replicate the Ombre tip out 🤯

#GeodesicFoilayage 

It’s surprisingly high impact with minimal foils! All the brightness is on the top surface and through the ends and all the depth is underneath for internal dimension 🤓

Ever struggled with Tint Bands?

This was my recent Live Demonstration model for my #GeodesicFoilayage class and she had a level 6 tint Ban with some traditional highlights.

Tips:
1. Break up the Line of Demarcation with Teasie-Lights to both pick out the dark as well as add gradience or Ombré through the ends
2. After 45mins processing, scrape off the old lightener and re-apply fresh to the areas that still need lift
3. Try a permanent Basebreaker in your ColorMelt formula starting at the line of demarcation to push out artificial pigment molecules and oxidize the natural pigment under the tint 🤯 ( Color cannot lift color, but it can “affect it” )

Formulas 🎨

ColorMelt @schwarzkopfusa TBH

Fun FACT : I was Awarded the @girlscouts GOLD the same year I graduated Beauty School 🏫 🤓

This is me at 18 years old. During my Senior year of Highschool I was in ROP Cosmetology, assisting in a Salon on Saturdays as an Intern, and achieved the highest award in Girl Scouts🥇 

So now you know I’m that kid that still wore a Scouts uniform past Elementary School 😅 

But I was never ashamed or hid it. I was proud to March to the beat of my own drum 🥁 

I loved GS and of course did my Troops hair whenever possible, including Camping trips 🏕 🤣

One of my favorite memories was when my Aunt Bonnie was a Guest Speaker. She told us the story of her first day at her job as an Engineer at Boeing when a male colleague came up to her asking for a cup of coffee. She simply said, “No, I’m an Engineer 👩‍💻 not your Secretary” 🗣

16 years later, I am a mother of 2 with a husband who quit his job as an Engineer to support our family business in the Beauty Industry 🙇🏼‍♀️

Thank you to all the women that empowered me, especially my Mom and my other Troop leaders @pamweber267 @carlottarzeb @mauilove53

Modern Partial Highlights👉

1. #HairlineShuffle to retouch Money Piece

* use a Gentle Oil based lightener, low volume peroxide, and a bond builder at the sensitive hairline 
Ex: @oligopro Lightening Creme 1:1 10vol & @olaplex 

2. Start the first highlight one fingers width behind the Money Piece on a Diagonal Back to create contrast 

*use a slightly stronger lightener and peroxide volume since the hair behind the hairline is more resistant.
Ex: @oligopro Cool Blonde 1:1 20vol & @olaplex 

3. Flip Up the Highlights to create a teasie-light underneath. This helps to also retouch the Ombré 

4. #JumpandPivot as you jump to the next section, pivot the angle of the diagonal until the last sections is horizontal at the crown 👸 - this takes less foils then a traditional Herringbone pattern and creates a ray of light effect 💡

5. Shadow Root and Gloss

Ex: Roots behind Money Piece @oligopro Calura Gloss 8NB & 7AI, Hairline-Mids-Ends 10NB

5. Treatment @k18hair

node.text:
Do you believe your life has a purpose?

Over 7 years ago I attended a prophetic church and received a prophecy that I “would be Respected among my Peers, and I would be Humble”

At the time I interpreted this to mean that I had the opportunity to gain the respect of my co-workers at the salon I held the title of Manager/Educator. Never did I think it could mean I would gain respect in my Industry on an International level 🙇🏼‍♀️

Nor did I understand that Humility would NOT come naturally, but the actual process of gaining success would be Humbling. On my path to becoming an Influencer I have become acutely aware of the major Responsibility there is in having the Power to Influence. 

The bigger the Hype, the more there is to live up to. And every spoken word has the ability to Bless or Lead Astray. 

Over the last seven years of traveling and teaching as an Independent Educator I have received both positive and constructive feedback. I have taken every single piece to Heart and take nothing for granted. 

There is a song by Francesca Battistelli, with a lyric that goes, “if I were looking for a Champion … I would understand if you chose everyone before me but that is just not my story” - He Knows My Name

It reminds me that this is all God’s Stage and in my experience, just like a good parent, He will bring me back down to Earth the minute I get cocky. But it also reminds me that I am Loved Unconditionally and my Labor is Not in Vein. 

These are some of the recent class reviews I have received. They Affirm my Purpose and Encourages me that I making a positive Impact 💥 

For me it’s more than just about Building a Brand, for me it is about leaving a Legacy. 

#ashleenormaneducates #ashleenormanacademy
